FBIS3-34726 "drnes030_p_94002" FBIS-NES-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Government Captures Four Posts; Rebels Bombard Kabul LD1002171894 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Dari 1600 GMT 10 Feb 94 LD1002171894 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network Language: Dari Article Type:BFN [Text] According to a report by a BAKHTAR military correspondent, as a result of the attack by forces of the Islamic army, four enemy posts have been captured in the direction of Chehelsotun by units of the Islamic army. [words indistinct] were killed in Jangalak and around Bala Hesar and a number of others were injured. To compensate for their repeated defeats, the infamous militia today targeted residential areas of Kabul City with savage rocket attacks. As a result a number of our innocent compatriots were killed or injured. In addition to the loss of lives, the landing of rockets caused much material damage too. The artillery of the Islamic army responded to the savage rocket attack of the infamous militia by crushing the enemy positions in Maranjan hill and Charasiab with heavy weapons fire. As a result extensive loss of life and heavy damage were inflicted on the infamous militia. According to another report, this morning an aeroplane of Dostam's militia stealthily bombarded residential areas of the city. Fortunately, it caused no loss of life, but much damage was inflicted on residential areas.
